ANTHRAX - MACEDONIA: (SKOPJE) BOVINE
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 3 Nov 2015
Source: OIE [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=19012


Information received on 3 Nov 2015 from Msc Zoran Popovski, director, Food and Veterinary Agency, Food and Veterinary Agency, Skopje, Former Yugoslavian Republic of Macedonia

Summary:
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 30 Oct 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 3 Nov 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 10/2007
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Raovikj, Saraj, SKOPJE
Date of start of the outbreak: 30 Oct 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 67 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Farm with 67 cattle, one cow died peracute on pasture and has been safely disposed of.

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 67 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 1.5 / 1.5 / 100 / 1.5
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures:
Measures applied: screening, disinfection/disinfestation, quarantine, no vaccination, no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Future reporting: the event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [See OIE website for their map].

